dataIdInfo.idAbs:
Enhanced data collection using LiDAR from the National Center for Airborne Laser Mapping sponsored by the National Science Foundation created an improved data framework for wetlands and ponds at the Archbold Biological Station. During this procedure an updated identification system was created. This system moves from general topographically interconnected wetlands to local extents of wetlands and ponds (individual basins and sites derived from contour partitions - basin and site rims). Earlier identifiers of points and polygons were cross referenced in the attribute table simplifying access to archived data.

This shapefile identifies wetland site candidates based on topographical data (depressions in the terrain). These sites may be active, dormant, or historic wetlands. Undisturbed areas (terrain depressions) in the data extent were historically (before they were improved) inundated at irregular intervals. Anthropogenic impact has rendered some sites extinct as wetlands and/or ponds.

In summary this shapefile does not identify wetlands and ponds but rather identifies probable candidates for such.
